data.enText: an official document that may be used to prove that the facts it states are true

data.chText: 出生 / 结婚 / 死亡证明

data.enText: an official document proving that you have completed a course of study or passed an exam; a qualification obtained after a course of study or an exam
data.chText: 文凭；结业证书；合格证书

data.enText: a Postgraduate Certificate in Education (= a British qualification for teachers)
data.chText: 教育学研究生证书（英国教师资格证书）

data.enText: to give sb an official document proving that they have successfully completed a training course, especially for a particular profession
data.chText: 发给结业证书；（尤指）发给职业培训证书

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

simple_means.memory_skill: cert 确实,确信 + -i- + fic 做,制作 + -ate 人/地位

ex.enText: The president has to sign his name on the document before it can become law.
ex.chText: 这份文件得由总统签名后才能成为法令。

ex.enText: You'd better save the document before closing it.
ex.chText: 你最好在关闭文档前先行保存。

synonyms.bx: 指记录官方信息的公文或计算机文档。

ex.enText: After 4 months' study, he was awarded a certificate.
ex.chText: 学习4个月之后，他被授予了结业证书。

ex.enText: Susan has a certificate in drama education.
ex.chText: 苏珊拥有戏剧教育资格证书。

synonyms.bx: 指证明某事真实性的官方文件；也指证明某人修完某一课程或通过某项考试的官方书面凭证。

ex.enText: The private college's charter was granted in 1985.
ex.chText: 这所私立大学的许可证是1985年颁发的。

synonyms.bx: 指政府或统治者准许成立组织、城镇、大学等并授予其特权的官方文件。

ex.enText: She got her teaching diploma last year.
ex.chText: 她去年拿到了教师证书。

ex.enText: You need to get your college diploma if you want to find a good job.
ex.chText: 想要找到好工作，你需要拿到大学毕业文凭。

ex.enText: My secretary has a diploma in marketing.
ex.chText: 我的秘书有市场营销专业的文凭。

ex.enText: I want to get a diploma in social work.
ex.chText: 我想拿一个社会福利工作方面的文凭。

synonyms.bx: 在英国英语里，指学完课程或通过考试之后获得的书面凭证；在美国英语里，指完成高中或大学学业之后获得的毕业证书或学位证书。

tr: a document attesting to the truth of certain stated facts
a formal declaration that documents a fact of relevance to finance and investment
the holder has a right to receive interest or dividends

value.def: A certificate is an official document stating that particular facts are true.

example.ex: To the right of the fireplace are various framed certificates.
example.tran: 壁炉的右边是各种镶框的证书。
教育学研究生毕业证书

value.def: A certificate is an official document that you receive when you have completed a course of study or training. The qualification that you receive is sometimes also called a certificate .
value.tran: 结业证书;合格证书;文凭
